<TITLE> <font color=black font size=1>REVIEW PETITIONS</font><br>SC hears second defence counsel</font> </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 25 (bdnews24.com)  The Supreme Court on Monday resumed hearing of review petitions by the five men sentenced to death for the 1975 murder of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman. A special four-member bench of the Supreme Court, headed by chief justice Md Tafazzul Islam, began the hearing at 9.30am. Abdur Rezzak Khan, lawyer for Sultan Shahriar Rashid Khan, presented his arguments on the second day of the simultaneous hearing on all five petitions. On the first day, the bench heard from Abdullah Al Mamun, counsel for convicts Bazlul Huda and AKM Mohiuddin Ahmed, on the day. Mamun argued for review of the appeal court's judgment, which last November upheld death penalties of the convicted killers, on 15 separate points. Among them, he asked the court to commute the death sentences of his two clients on grounds of old age. b
